cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of measuring the generalization capacity of image classifiers, which is a central problem in machine learning. The paper presents a public dataset of microscopy images and benchmarks a range of classification models using different representations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with the challenges of covariate shifts in image data, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of neural networks in the classification models could also make it relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of microscopy images could make it relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
